AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - GEORGIA (09): OIE
****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 20 Aug 2007
Source: OIE WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database) Disease
Information 2007; 20(34) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>

African swine fever, Georgia
-------------------------------
Information received on 17 Aug 2007 from Dr. Levan Ramishvili,
Chairman of the Veterinary Union, Veterinary Union, Ministry of
Agriculture, Tbilisi, Georgia
Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date 3 Jul 2007
Date of confirmation of event 3 Aug 2007
Report date 17 Aug 2007
Date submitted to OIE 20 Aug 2007
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
Report pertains to: Defined zone within the country
New outbreaks
New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Latta, Gulripish, ABKHAZIA AUTONOMOUS REPUBLIC
Date of start of outbreak 4 Jul 2007
Outbreak status Resolved (29 Jul 2007)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Species Swine
Susceptible 200
Cases 161
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 39
Affected population free-range swine of private owners
Outbreak 2 Babushari, Gulripish, ABKHAZIA AUTONOMOUS REPUBLIC
Date of start of outbreak 4 Jul 2007
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Species Swine
Susceptible 200
Cases 180
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 20
Affected population free-range swine of private owners
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 2
Outbreak Location: ABKHAZIA AUTONOMOUS REPUBLIC (Latta, Gulripish;
Babushari, Gulripish)
Total animals affected:
Species Swine
Susceptible 400
Cases 341
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 59
Outbreak statistics
Species Swine
Apparent morbidity rate 85.25 percent
Apparent mortality rate 0.00 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 0.00 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 14.75 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction or slaughter
Epidemiology: Source of infection. Fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)
Epidemiological comments: In Babushari, control measures are to be applied.
Control measures:
Measures already applied: Movement control inside the country;
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); Quarantine;
Vaccination permitted; No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: None specified
Laboratory name and type: Federal Scientific Institution All-Russia
Scientific Institute of Veterinary Virology and Microbiology, Pokrov
(Russia) (Local laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species Swine
Test enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA)
Test date 6 Aug 2007
Result Positive
Species Swine
Test Swine indirect fluorescent antibody (IFA) test
Test date 6 Aug 2007
Result Positive
Species Swine
Test Swine polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date 3 Aug 2007
Result Positive
Species Swine
Test Swine virus isolation
Test date 6 Aug 2007
Result Positive
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
[A link to all the OIE reports in the country including a map of all
previous outbreaks can be obtained at OIE WAHID event summary at
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=event_summary&reportid=5720>.
The above report is the 1st to come from the Abkhazia Autonomous
Republic region and was, in fact, requested by the ProMED-mail
posting 20070817.2689 a few days ago. The timely submission is much
appreciated because of the serious nature of this trans-boundary
disease. Moreover, this is the 1st report from the most western
region of the country.
A good synopsis of African swine fever is given by "African swine
fever - Georgia (02): OIE 20070608.1860" referenced below. - Mod.PC]
